<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508218>
    dc:description "FIGURES 305−308. Luciola pallidipes male. 305−308 aedeagal sheath: 305 dorsal (arrow indicates prolonged margin of sheath tergite; aedeagus removed); 306−308 aedeagal sheath with aedeagus: 306 right lateral (arrow indicates prolonged margin of sheath tergite); 307 dorsal; 308 ventral (arrows indicate leaf like lobes from LL of aedeagus). Scale lines are 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3508218/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508204>
    dc:description "FIGURES 258−269. Luciola horni males. 258, 259, 269 type male; 260−265, 267, 268 Halupahani male (NHML); 266 India male (Prague). 258, 266, 267 habitus dorsal; 259 habitus ventral; 260, 261, 265 aedeagal sheath: 260 ventral; 261, 265 dorsal (260, 261 under transmitted light from below); 262, 263 aedeagus: 262 ventral; 263 right lateral; 268 tergites 7, 8 dorsal; 269 label. Scale lines are 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3508204/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

